ce:section.ce:para:
The alloys with Ti/(Cr+Fe) ratio of 0.9–1.1 are found to be single-phases with BCC structures (as seen in Fig. 6
), and the lattice parameters increase linearly with the increase of the ratio (as seen in Fig. 7
), which is accordant with Section 3.2 and can explain the decrease of the plateau pressure when the ratio increases.
